SIMPLE: etymologize
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Etymologize
<hw>Et`y*mol"o*gize</hw> <pr>(-j⟦imac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧tymologiser</ets>.]</ety> <def>To give the
etymology of; to trace to the root or primitive, as a word.</def>
<rj><au>Camden</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etymologize</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Etymologize
<hw>Et`y*mol"o*gize</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To search into the
origin of words; to deduce words from their simple roots.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How perilous it is to <qex>etymologize</qex> at random.</q>
<rj><qau>Trench.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Etymology</ent>⟦br⟧
